               <head>Makhzan al-fava'id</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Makhzan al-favāʾid by Ḥafīẓ al-Dīn Aḥmad ibn Hilāl al-Dīn Muḥammad al-Ṣiddīqī al-Barduvānī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100087 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85076229 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85010050" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3929-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7143">Ḥafīẓ al-Dīn Aḥmad ibn Hilāl al-Dīn Muḥammad al-Ṣiddīqī al-Barduvānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7143" type="supplied">حفيظ الدّين احمد ابن هلال الدّين محمّد الصّدّيقى البردوانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21911">Makhzan al-favāʾid</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21911">مخزن الفوائد</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Manual of <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">inshāʾ</term> or epistolography, including numerous anecdotes
                        </p>
                        <p>Text is prefaced with a sketch of the author's autobiography, detailing his years of service for the East India Company</p>
                        <p>The work is dedicated to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_35251879" role="dte">Lord William Bentinck</persName>, and completed in <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">1246</date> / <date calendar="Gregorian">1830-1</date>
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                        <p>Apparently an <term xml:lang="en">autograph</term>
                        </p>
                        <p>No other copies appear to be recorded</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
